The suspect being led out of a hospital in Kitengela. [Peterson Githaiga, Standard]  A man who reportedly disappeared moments before his wife was found dead in Kikumbo village, Kalama sub-County, in Machakos has been arrested.  The suspect is said to have attempted to take poison after he was arrested in Mlolongo town on Thursday, and was taken to Saitoti Level Four Hospital in Kajiado County.  Upon discharge, the police took him to Machakos Police Station for questioning.  Machakos sub-County DCIO Simon Waithaka said he will be arraigned soon.  The police have been investigating circumstances under which the 35-year-old woman died last Friday  The man and the victim visited his parents at Kikumbo village last Friday and went to bed after taking their meals. But the following day, the woman was found dead in their bed and the man was missing.  Her body was found in a pool of blood and had deep panga cuts. Police recovered a machete believed to be the murder weapon in a toilet within the homestead.  By Irissheel Shanzu | 4 hours ago By Daniel Chege | 5 hours ago By Olivia Odhiambo | 1 day ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 1 day ago